1
00:00:01,560 --> 00:00:03,520
"Jee is so worried
he's hallucinating."

2
00:00:04,320 --> 00:00:07,022
"He definitely won't
be able to sleep tonight."

3
00:00:07,047 --> 00:00:08,800
You like this outdated style?

4
00:00:08,825 --> 00:00:11,602
You don't look very tech-savvy.

5
00:00:11,627 --> 00:00:14,640
I thought you were
Mr. Jira's secretary.

6
00:00:14,665 --> 00:00:17,633
Age isn't an indicator
of work quality, is it?

7
00:00:18,656 --> 00:00:21,169
She couldn't remember her lines.
She kept forgetting.

8
00:00:21,169 --> 00:00:23,455
I wonder if she has Alzheimer's.

9
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:27,353
If later on,
we forget each other...

10
00:00:27,378 --> 00:00:29,680
What hasn't happened yet,
don't worry about it.

11
00:01:00,103 --> 00:01:01,103
Old Man,

12
00:01:02,001 --> 00:01:03,120
is something wrong?

13
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:19,503
Don't you pretend to be asleep.

14
00:01:21,360 --> 00:01:24,023
What's bothering you?

15
00:01:29,917 --> 00:01:32,120
"Why can't I sleep tonight?"

16
00:02:07,552 --> 00:02:08,880
Hi there.

17
00:02:11,723 --> 00:02:13,496
Oops! Ow!

18
00:02:13,521 --> 00:02:14,521
Are you okay?

19
00:02:15,079 --> 00:02:17,704
My shoe came apart.

20
00:02:17,704 --> 00:02:20,214
Looks like I need to glue it.

21
00:02:20,239 --> 00:02:22,681
I have flip-flops.

22
00:02:22,706 --> 00:02:24,080
- Really?
- Want to borrow them?

23
00:02:26,139 --> 00:02:27,960
Hang on.

24
00:02:28,766 --> 00:02:30,679
Thank you.

25
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:33,880
- Here you go.
- Let me try.

26
00:02:34,957 --> 00:02:35,957
Yeah, okay.

27
00:02:36,645 --> 00:02:38,520
- Fit?
- Yeah.

28
00:02:38,545 --> 00:02:39,800
- Thanks.
- Mmm.

29
00:02:40,308 --> 00:02:42,600
- Comfortable...
- Hey!

30
00:02:42,625 --> 00:02:44,216
You broke them!

31
00:02:46,744 --> 00:02:47,960
- Oof...
- I...

32
00:02:49,775 --> 00:02:53,022
- Here.
- I can't wear them anymore.

33
00:02:53,022 --> 00:02:54,320
So what are you going to wear?

34
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:57,916
- Jira, which color do you prefer?
- Hmm?

35
00:02:58,375 --> 00:03:01,800
I think these two colors
would go well together.

36
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:04,400
- These two.
- Got it. Thank you.

37
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:07,513
Hot Americano for you.

38
00:03:07,513 --> 00:03:08,560
Okay.

39
00:03:09,024 --> 00:03:11,651
- Oops! I'm so sorry!
- Oh no!

40
00:03:11,651 --> 00:03:14,017
- I didn't mean to.
- It's okay.

41
00:03:14,589 --> 00:03:16,520
Ugh...

42
00:03:17,779 --> 00:03:19,503
Jira's having a rough day.

43
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:21,853
- Bad luck, maybe.
- Bad luck?

44
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:24,700
Yeah. I rode the elevator
with him earlier.

45
00:03:24,700 --> 00:03:26,463
He even got caught in the doors.

46
00:03:26,488 --> 00:03:27,848
I was in the elevator with you.

47
00:03:27,848 --> 00:03:30,840
He got caught
because you didn't hold for him.

48
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:34,360
Don't blame luck. Get back to work.

49
00:03:34,818 --> 00:03:36,465
It's fine.

50
00:03:36,465 --> 00:03:38,411
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

51
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,455
This is really hard to choose.

52
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:04,820
- Jira.
- Hmm?

53
00:04:04,820 --> 00:04:07,493
- The client hasn't responded.
- Why?

54
00:04:07,493 --> 00:04:10,920
I've been messaging them,
but they haven't replied.

55
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:12,520
What do we do now?

56
00:04:13,117 --> 00:04:14,607
- Jee?
- Yes?

57
00:04:14,607 --> 00:04:16,280
Can we talk?

58
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:17,614
Yes, sure.

59
00:04:17,975 --> 00:04:20,640
- I'll leave this with you.
- Sure.

60
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,800
Don't tell me...

61
00:04:33,589 --> 00:04:37,070
No way.
He's too good at his job.

62
00:04:37,095 --> 00:04:39,468
Besides, he's been here forever.

63
00:04:39,468 --> 00:04:42,808
That's exactly why.
His salary must be high.

64
00:04:42,808 --> 00:04:46,575
If the company wants to cut costs,
who do you think they'll let go?

65
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:49,080
You, first. The most useless.

66
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:51,667
Oh please.
You're the most useless one.

67
00:04:51,667 --> 00:04:55,476
- Hey, watch it.
- Stop it. No fighting.

68
00:04:55,742 --> 00:04:59,716
All our salaries combined
still might not equal Jira's.

69
00:05:00,595 --> 00:05:01,720
True.

70
00:05:02,589 --> 00:05:05,742
How depressing!
We should get back to work?

71
00:05:08,280 --> 00:05:09,586
Please have a seat.

72
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:19,823
Jee, you're know that we
are struggling right now, right?

73
00:05:22,921 --> 00:05:23,921
Yes.

74
00:05:23,921 --> 00:05:26,675
Ms. Praw has started
putting pressure on me

75
00:05:26,675 --> 00:05:28,840
since the sales dropped.

76
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:31,787
She wants every department
to help reduce costs.

77
00:05:31,787 --> 00:05:35,927
Production is already
doing everything they can.

78
00:05:35,927 --> 00:05:40,067
If we lower our prices
to compete with Chinese factories,

79
00:05:40,067 --> 00:05:41,360
we'll all go under.

80
00:05:43,033 --> 00:05:47,241
These days, people don't
really care much about quality.

81
00:05:47,266 --> 00:05:51,842
They don't care what kind
of fabric or materials are used.

82
00:05:51,867 --> 00:05:54,692
No matter
how good the stitching is...

83
00:05:56,920 --> 00:06:00,273
Fast fashion has
taken over the market.

84
00:06:00,298 --> 00:06:02,698
Exactly. That's why
Ms. Praw is pressuring us.

85
00:06:02,698 --> 00:06:04,520
We may have to downsize.

86
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:06,896
Or possibly let someone go.

87
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:10,147
Me?

88
00:06:10,147 --> 00:06:15,000
We're still in discussions,
trying to find the best solution.

89
00:06:15,447 --> 00:06:18,695
I'm doing everything I can.

90
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:19,800
But Jee,

91
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:22,480
I just wanted to
let you know in advance

92
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:24,575
so you can prepare,

93
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:26,310
just in case.

94
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,560
Jee?

95
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:36,960
Are you okay?

96
00:06:41,075 --> 00:06:42,747
They bought it.

97
00:06:43,415 --> 00:06:44,760
Here he is.

98
00:06:45,298 --> 00:06:47,135
Wow, what is that?

99
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,600
- Jee.
- Hey, bro.

100
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,699
Hi, Dad.

101
00:06:49,723 --> 00:06:51,863
- Hi, son.
- I brought grilled prawns.

102
00:06:51,863 --> 00:06:53,850
- Oh, thank you, son.
- Prawns!

103
00:06:53,850 --> 00:06:56,360
- Sure.
- Lucky me.

104
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:59,411
Coming home today
and having prawns too.

105
00:06:59,436 --> 00:07:02,183
I mean seeing Jee. I missed you.

106
00:07:02,183 --> 00:07:04,597
- Listen to her.
- She's got a whiff of the prawns.

107
00:07:04,597 --> 00:07:06,323
Let me put them on a plate.

108
00:07:06,323 --> 00:07:09,231
Careful. You'll break the head.

109
00:07:12,355 --> 00:07:15,183
Peeling prawns technique.

110
00:07:15,596 --> 00:07:17,339
Whoa...

111
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:20,280
Aren't you going to peel some
for your youngest son?

112
00:07:21,809 --> 00:07:23,560
The middle child
never gets any either, Mom.

113
00:07:24,006 --> 00:07:27,396
He bought them, right?

114
00:07:27,886 --> 00:07:31,943
If you didn't pay for it,
then work for it.

115
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:34,873
I'm not taking side on this one,

116
00:07:34,873 --> 00:07:36,233
but Mom's right.

117
00:07:36,233 --> 00:07:37,320
Mmm.

118
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:40,809
Fine then.
The bathroom renovation...

119
00:07:40,834 --> 00:07:43,128
let Mom's favorite son pay for it.

120
00:07:43,153 --> 00:07:44,423
Bathroom renovation?

121
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:51,276
I was thinking of fixing up
the bathroom a little bit.

122
00:07:51,735 --> 00:07:53,320
A little bit?

123
00:07:53,345 --> 00:07:56,880
The contractor said
it's really old.

124
00:07:56,880 --> 00:07:59,596
We might have to redo
the whole plumbing system.

125
00:08:00,540 --> 00:08:02,423
That's going to cost a lot, Dad.

126
00:08:03,131 --> 00:08:05,320
I can cover it.

127
00:08:05,844 --> 00:08:08,491
Thank you so much, son.

128
00:08:08,491 --> 00:08:13,856
Having a good child you can rely on
is the greatest happiness.

129
00:08:13,881 --> 00:08:15,525
Unlike these two.

130
00:08:16,110 --> 00:08:20,028
Mom, we have kids to raise.

131
00:08:20,028 --> 00:08:22,320
Tuition these days
is insanely expensive.

132
00:08:22,345 --> 00:08:25,565
Mine have summer classes too.

133
00:08:25,565 --> 00:08:28,785
Horse riding, fencing,
piano lessons, hip-hop lessons,

134
00:08:28,785 --> 00:08:30,855
so many extra classes.

135
00:08:30,880 --> 00:08:33,600
I'm lucky. My youngest
is almost done with university.

136
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,927
Soon I'll finally get a break

137
00:08:35,927 --> 00:08:37,153
…maybe.

138
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:40,987
I envy people without kids.

139
00:08:40,987 --> 00:08:42,200
Really. Really.

140
00:08:43,961 --> 00:08:47,252
I envy people without kids…

141
00:08:47,277 --> 00:08:48,576
Really.

142
00:08:48,601 --> 00:08:51,610
- Hey, Dad...
- Dad, what about us?

143
00:08:52,293 --> 00:08:53,750
What's my name again?

144
00:08:53,775 --> 00:08:55,947
I forgot.

145
00:08:55,947 --> 00:08:57,946
It's me, Jang, your daughter.

146
00:08:57,946 --> 00:09:00,680
- Oh, Jang.
- Right...

147
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:01,905
Eat, dear.

148
00:09:01,905 --> 00:09:03,738
- I'll peel more for you.
- Okay.

149
00:09:03,738 --> 00:09:05,744
- Don't.
- Let Mom peel it.

150
00:09:11,309 --> 00:09:14,150
- Here
- Put them here.

151
00:09:14,175 --> 00:09:16,253
- Yeah.
- Thanks.

152
00:09:16,253 --> 00:09:17,617
- Bro.
- Hmm?

153
00:09:17,617 --> 00:09:20,137
We can help chip in
for the bathroom renovation.

154
00:09:20,137 --> 00:09:24,025
It's fine. I'm the eldest.

155
00:09:24,025 --> 00:09:26,256
Whoa! Sugar Daddy!

156
00:09:26,281 --> 00:09:28,501
Jee, when will you get married?

157
00:09:28,501 --> 00:09:30,348
What kind of question is that?

158
00:09:30,348 --> 00:09:33,414
Come on, you can get married now.

159
00:09:33,414 --> 00:09:35,295
We have marriage equality now.

160
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:38,007
Just because we can
doesn't mean we have to.

161
00:09:38,007 --> 00:09:39,729
It's just like any couple.

162
00:09:39,729 --> 00:09:43,560
We have to
be sure and be ready first.

163
00:09:43,560 --> 00:09:47,120
Gosh. You've been together so long.
When will you be sure or ready?

164
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:51,123
Is it you or Ohn who
doesn't want to get married?

165
00:09:51,520 --> 00:09:52,806
What?

166
00:09:54,106 --> 00:09:55,112
Wait...

167
00:09:56,154 --> 00:09:57,735
Are you getting married?

168
00:09:57,735 --> 00:10:00,280
Wait! No, Mom. Not that.

169
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:04,242
I was just asking him
when he is going to get married

170
00:10:04,242 --> 00:10:06,415
since he's been
with Ohn for so long.

171
00:10:07,895 --> 00:10:08,960
Well...

172
00:10:09,713 --> 00:10:11,340
Why haven't you married him yet?

173
00:10:16,261 --> 00:10:19,270
Ever since she heard
about Auntie Pannee...

174
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:27,000
Do you want me...

175
00:10:30,381 --> 00:10:32,410
to marry Ohn?

176
00:10:33,160 --> 00:10:34,976
If you want to, then do it.

177
00:10:35,344 --> 00:10:36,840
You can get married now.

178
00:10:38,119 --> 00:10:40,535
But if you don't want to,

179
00:10:40,560 --> 00:10:42,640
I won't nag you anymore.

180
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:45,200
Listen...

181
00:10:46,231 --> 00:10:49,080
If you don't marry Ohn,
I feel bad for him.

182
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:51,601
He's a good man.
He loves you very much.

183
00:10:51,626 --> 00:10:54,090
If you're not serious about him...

184
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,575
then let him go.

185
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,353
Let him find someone good.
Find better opportunities.

186
00:10:59,353 --> 00:11:03,280
Or do you have someone else?

187
00:11:03,280 --> 00:11:05,310
- Keeping your options open?
- Jee!

188
00:11:05,649 --> 00:11:07,791
- Yeah.
- Are you a playboy?

189
00:11:07,791 --> 00:11:10,760
No, Mom. Hold on...

190
00:11:10,760 --> 00:11:13,080
Marriage is a big deal.

191
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:16,967
Shouldn't we wait
until we're stable?

192
00:11:16,967 --> 00:11:19,580
Oh, please.
You both have good jobs.

193
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:21,547
How much more stable
do you need to be?

194
00:11:21,547 --> 00:11:24,131
- Yeah. Is that just an excuse?
- Right.

195
00:11:24,156 --> 00:11:27,059
Don't break Ohn's heart.

196
00:11:27,084 --> 00:11:28,497
- Jee.
- Huh?

197
00:11:29,588 --> 00:11:31,320
Are you worried about Mom and Dad?

198
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:34,926
- It's not like that at all.
- Then what is it?

199
00:11:36,978 --> 00:11:39,283
Enough. I'm going home. It's late.

200
00:11:39,317 --> 00:11:41,344
- Oh, come on.
- I'm leaving.

201
00:11:41,344 --> 00:11:43,855
See? Always running away.

202
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:45,480
Go on. Drive safe, son.

203
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:47,800
- Bye, Jee.
- Bye, Jee. Bye.

204
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:51,459
- Cheers!
- Yay!

205
00:11:51,459 --> 00:11:54,209
Cheers!

206
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:58,200
Yes!

207
00:12:01,098 --> 00:12:02,560
What's the occasion?

208
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:06,360
Your comeback.

209
00:12:06,694 --> 00:12:07,987
- That's right.
- Yeah.

210
00:12:08,012 --> 00:12:12,200
At the hospital, my friends
are all talking about your comics.

211
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:15,413
Kittima is popular again.

212
00:12:15,413 --> 00:12:18,940
People are searching for it
like it's a collectible.

213
00:12:18,940 --> 00:12:23,000
Sellers are jacking up the prices.
People are getting scammed.

214
00:12:24,224 --> 00:12:26,253
Is this a comic book or a Labubu?

215
00:12:27,851 --> 00:12:29,910
It's nothing like Labubu.

216
00:12:30,520 --> 00:12:34,316
People are just hyped.
The trend will fade soon.

217
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:37,037
Exactly!

218
00:12:37,061 --> 00:12:39,710
Strike while the iron is hot.

219
00:12:40,266 --> 00:12:41,606
Seize the opportunity.

220
00:12:41,606 --> 00:12:43,493
Sell, sell, sell!

221
00:12:43,493 --> 00:12:46,210
Whatever you can sell, sell it.

222
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:50,200
I heard the editor said that...

223
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:54,816
they'll print on the cover
of the new comic book,

224
00:12:54,841 --> 00:12:59,640
"By the author of Kittima,
the Witch of the Enchanted City."

225
00:13:05,114 --> 00:13:07,200
Why don't you look happy?

226
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:10,703
She's even happier than you.

227
00:13:11,880 --> 00:13:12,880
I don't know.

228
00:13:16,258 --> 00:13:17,504
Did you fight with Jee?

229
00:13:20,615 --> 00:13:21,680
No.

230
00:13:22,888 --> 00:13:23,888
It's just...

231
00:13:24,308 --> 00:13:25,560
It's...

232
00:13:26,263 --> 00:13:27,323
Hmm...

233
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:29,360
Well...

234
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:32,520
The thing is...

235
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:35,920
I don't know how to say it.

236
00:13:35,920 --> 00:13:38,855
You're driving me crazy!

237
00:13:38,880 --> 00:13:42,767
Please just say it.
I want to know.

238
00:13:42,767 --> 00:13:45,467
Spit it out.

239
00:13:45,467 --> 00:13:46,540
Hmm.

240
00:13:48,385 --> 00:13:49,472
You know...

241
00:13:50,495 --> 00:13:52,480
that my comics became
popular again because...

242
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:55,440
Jee created a blog for me.

243
00:14:09,742 --> 00:14:11,108
"Keep on fighting!"

244
00:14:14,760 --> 00:14:17,416
He helped bring me
back into the spotlight.

245
00:14:18,191 --> 00:14:19,311
But I...

246
00:14:20,088 --> 00:14:22,103
I can't help him
with anything at all.

247
00:14:23,290 --> 00:14:25,040
I want to cry.

248
00:14:25,065 --> 00:14:27,240
What's this?

249
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:37,149
Being unemployed at this age

250
00:14:37,174 --> 00:14:39,238
must be quite difficult.

251
00:14:39,263 --> 00:14:41,003
Applying for a new job is hard.

252
00:14:41,003 --> 00:14:44,520
Companies prefer new graduates
because they're cheaper.

253
00:14:45,639 --> 00:14:47,943
They have a hard time
finding jobs now as well.

254
00:14:48,842 --> 00:14:49,939
Hmm.

255
00:14:50,654 --> 00:14:52,520
Jee loves his work so much.

256
00:14:52,967 --> 00:14:55,034
He's more dedicated than anyone.

257
00:14:55,034 --> 00:14:57,120
If he really loses his job,

258
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:58,710
he'll definitely be devastated.

259
00:14:59,584 --> 00:15:00,719
I feel bad for him.

260
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:03,397
Honestly,

261
00:15:03,397 --> 00:15:06,564
I always thought
that between you and Jee,

262
00:15:06,564 --> 00:15:09,135
he would be the breadwinner.

263
00:15:09,160 --> 00:15:12,880
Whoa, do I look so incapable

264
00:15:12,880 --> 00:15:15,253
that I have to rely
on a rich boyfriend?

265
00:15:15,253 --> 00:15:16,680
- Yes.
- Ouch!

266
00:15:19,669 --> 00:15:20,769
Hmm...

267
00:15:21,723 --> 00:15:22,723
What if...

268
00:15:23,739 --> 00:15:25,643
Jee really loses his job,

269
00:15:26,462 --> 00:15:28,256
it will show him that

270
00:15:28,907 --> 00:15:31,120
I'm always by his side

271
00:15:32,189 --> 00:15:34,795
whether rich or poor...

272
00:15:35,498 --> 00:15:37,619
happy or sad.

273
00:15:37,644 --> 00:15:40,960
Even if we have to brave
storms and rain together.

274
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:43,323
It will surely...

275
00:15:44,481 --> 00:15:47,080
make us love each other even more.

276
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:52,560
Scenario

277
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:54,166
Number One.

278
00:15:56,880 --> 00:15:59,000
Oh, no...

279
00:15:59,025 --> 00:16:02,947
I've lost my job.
I've failed. I'm worthless.

280
00:16:02,972 --> 00:16:05,095
But you still have me.

281
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:07,180
Even though I have
nothing to give you,

282
00:16:07,180 --> 00:16:08,960
we still have each other.

283
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:11,223
Even if we have no food to eat,

284
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:14,592
we'll weather the storm together.

285
00:16:14,617 --> 00:16:16,760
- Ohn...
- Jee...

286
00:16:16,760 --> 00:16:18,592
Oh, my darling.

287
00:16:18,617 --> 00:16:21,480
You are the candlelight of my life.

288
00:16:22,791 --> 00:16:25,066
I'm gonna puke. So delusional.

289
00:16:25,091 --> 00:16:26,758
So naïve.

290
00:16:26,783 --> 00:16:30,920
Kindergarteners have
more complex thoughts than this.

291
00:16:34,518 --> 00:16:37,455
You have quite a sharp tongue.

292
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:39,240
Don't copy Chon.

293
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:41,238
She's sharper than me.

294
00:16:41,263 --> 00:16:43,530
Wait until you're close to her.

295
00:16:45,813 --> 00:16:49,455
Then let's keep our distance.

296
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:52,340
Social distancing is better.

297
00:16:52,340 --> 00:16:55,510
Ohn, come back.

298
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:59,520
Come to think of it,
for most couples,

299
00:16:59,520 --> 00:17:01,535
if not breaking up
because of an affair,

300
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:03,175
it's because of money.

301
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:05,396
Love doesn't make you full.

302
00:17:05,840 --> 00:17:07,160
When times get tough,

303
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:10,910
the dark side reveals itself.

304
00:17:11,535 --> 00:17:12,535
Dark side?

305
00:17:15,294 --> 00:17:16,760
Oh, Jee.

306
00:17:17,721 --> 00:17:18,728
Hmm?

307
00:17:18,728 --> 00:17:21,135
You sleep and watch TV all day.

308
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:23,735
Don't you think about
making a living at all?

309
00:17:23,760 --> 00:17:25,160
Hey...

310
00:17:26,388 --> 00:17:27,796
What do you want me to do?

311
00:17:28,912 --> 00:17:32,980
Just get a job!

312
00:17:33,005 --> 00:17:34,791
Don't just ask for money
to buy booze

313
00:17:34,791 --> 00:17:36,265
and bet on online football.

314
00:17:36,265 --> 00:17:37,703
Hey!

315
00:17:38,598 --> 00:17:40,910
- Leave me alone.
- Stop betting.

316
00:17:40,935 --> 00:17:42,907
- Kicking?
- You kick me?

317
00:17:42,907 --> 00:17:44,815
- You lousy husband!
- Ouch!

318
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:46,959
Fighting tooth and nail.

319
00:17:46,984 --> 00:17:48,880
See?

320
00:17:51,598 --> 00:17:54,095
No, this isn't it.

321
00:17:54,120 --> 00:17:55,560
It's a bit out of his character.

322
00:17:56,299 --> 00:18:00,375
No matter how tough things get,
he wouldn't bet on football.

323
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:02,055
He doesn't even watch it.

324
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:03,080
Yeah, true.

325
00:18:04,418 --> 00:18:06,083
I think it would go another way.

326
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:07,720
Another way?

327
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:11,573
Scenario

328
00:18:11,573 --> 00:18:13,163
Number Three

329
00:18:21,080 --> 00:18:22,926
- Ohn.
- Jee.

330
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:26,700
Let's break up.

331
00:18:27,691 --> 00:18:29,495
Break up?

332
00:18:29,520 --> 00:18:31,055
Why?

333
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:32,393
You're too good for me.

334
00:18:32,393 --> 00:18:35,923
You have a bright future,
but I have nothing left.

335
00:18:36,840 --> 00:18:37,880
It's okay, Jee.

336
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:42,311
We'll get through this together.
Everything will be better.

337
00:18:42,336 --> 00:18:44,680
I'm famous again now.

338
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:46,703
I'll make lots of money.

339
00:18:47,579 --> 00:18:50,983
Don't worry. I'll support you.

340
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:54,416
Even if I have nothing left,

341
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:58,203
please let me keep my dignity.

342
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:00,520
Ohn.

343
00:19:02,120 --> 00:19:05,360
- Farewell.
- No, Jee! No...

344
00:19:06,200 --> 00:19:09,476
This scenario seems very plausible.

345
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:15,680
Do you think Ohn
is too good for Jee?

346
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:18,216
Not at all.

347
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:21,851
Whatever.

348
00:19:21,875 --> 00:19:24,226
Jee isn't that melodramatic.

349
00:19:24,690 --> 00:19:28,924
But your version of him
is super melodramatic.

350
00:19:28,924 --> 00:19:32,086
True. You have to
admit it's possible.

351
00:19:32,111 --> 00:19:36,294
A proud man like him
might act exactly like we think.

352
00:19:36,327 --> 00:19:38,320
- Or it's...
- Jee!

353
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:40,503
- You're back?
- Hmm?

354
00:19:41,054 --> 00:19:42,294
- Hello.
- Jee!

355
00:19:42,294 --> 00:19:44,108
Oh, hello.

356
00:19:44,133 --> 00:19:47,507
- We stopped by for a little chat.
- Yeah, right.

357
00:19:47,507 --> 00:19:49,425
Just gossiping.

358
00:19:50,425 --> 00:19:53,780
Make yourselves at home.

359
00:19:53,805 --> 00:19:56,377
I bought some grilled prawns.

360
00:19:56,402 --> 00:19:59,005
Wow, thank you.

361
00:19:59,005 --> 00:20:02,400
- But we just ate.
- Oh.

362
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:03,720
Just leave them here for now.

363
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:05,763
I'll put them
in the fridge for tomorrow.

364
00:20:07,568 --> 00:20:08,606
Okay.

365
00:20:09,762 --> 00:20:11,720
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

366
00:20:11,720 --> 00:20:12,760
Okay then...

367
00:20:13,993 --> 00:20:15,960
- Excuse me.
- Sure.

368
00:20:20,795 --> 00:20:24,783
He's about to lose his job,
but still has money for prawns?

369
00:20:24,808 --> 00:20:27,535
Maybe it's his last supper.

370
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:28,670
- Ugh!
- Ouch!

371
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:30,304
You two!

372
00:20:30,304 --> 00:20:32,337
He still has his job.

373
00:20:40,498 --> 00:20:42,360
Jee seems off today.

374
00:20:43,622 --> 00:20:44,680
How so?

375
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:47,480
Doesn't he look stressed?

376
00:20:48,920 --> 00:20:49,920
Really?

377
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:53,303
Could it be about Ohn?

378
00:20:55,406 --> 00:20:56,966
It must be about Ohn.

379
00:20:58,332 --> 00:20:59,530
Did they fight?

380
00:21:02,182 --> 00:21:03,576
They definitely fought.

381
00:21:05,920 --> 00:21:07,600
Don't jump to conclusions.

382
00:21:08,787 --> 00:21:10,330
It might be nothing.

383
00:21:10,689 --> 00:21:12,910
How can I not?

384
00:21:13,520 --> 00:21:17,623
When he's troubled,
he never tells us anything anyway.

385
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:20,400
Dear.

386
00:21:22,300 --> 00:21:23,680
I think Jee...

387
00:21:25,089 --> 00:21:28,375
probably just afraid
we'd get worried too.

388
00:21:30,327 --> 00:21:31,346
Hmm.

389
00:21:32,390 --> 00:21:34,096
That might be true.

390
00:21:44,583 --> 00:21:45,583
Jee.

391
00:21:47,202 --> 00:21:49,623
If you really lose your job,

392
00:21:50,120 --> 00:21:51,436
it'll be okay.

393
00:21:52,050 --> 00:21:54,400
It's not. It won't be okay.

394
00:21:57,612 --> 00:21:58,800
Hmm...

395
00:21:59,229 --> 00:22:00,480
Who was it?

396
00:22:01,247 --> 00:22:05,056
Was it Mr. Tony? The one who
invited you to work in Singapore.

397
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:08,420
You could go now.

398
00:22:08,420 --> 00:22:10,720
Just tell him
you changed your mind.

399
00:22:13,574 --> 00:22:14,594
No.

400
00:22:14,594 --> 00:22:17,641
I can move to Singapore with you.

401
00:22:17,641 --> 00:22:18,800
Nah.

402
00:22:19,820 --> 00:22:22,453
I turned him down
so coldly back then.

403
00:22:22,453 --> 00:22:25,120
I can't ask him for a job now.

404
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:27,880
Come on, what's the big deal?

405
00:22:27,880 --> 00:22:29,400
Why be so proud?

406
00:22:29,920 --> 00:22:31,600
What does it matter?

407
00:22:32,045 --> 00:22:36,735
In that case, should I go
ask that Bully Boy for a job?

408
00:22:36,760 --> 00:22:38,600
No way!

409
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:46,032
Listen, even if we have to
eat rice with only fish sauce,

410
00:22:46,057 --> 00:22:49,480
you are not to work with that bully.

411
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:50,560
Understand?

412
00:22:51,160 --> 00:22:52,280
See?

413
00:22:53,499 --> 00:22:57,216
Some options are
just hard to swallow.

414
00:23:07,960 --> 00:23:09,040
Jee.

415
00:23:12,280 --> 00:23:15,040
Chon wants to invite us
to see a fortune teller.

416
00:23:17,041 --> 00:23:18,510
Fortune teller?

417
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:21,003
If you want to go,
go ahead. I'll pass.

418
00:23:21,760 --> 00:23:23,280
Why?

419
00:23:23,783 --> 00:23:28,506
Chon said this one is famous.

420
00:23:28,531 --> 00:23:31,160
Very accurate and powerful.

421
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:33,000
Millions of followers.

422
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,223
So what?

423
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:36,680
What about the last time you went?

424
00:23:37,284 --> 00:23:38,757
They said
I'd break up with you.

425
00:23:39,269 --> 00:23:42,240
That's utter nonsense.
Completely unreliable.

426
00:23:42,675 --> 00:23:46,600
It doesn't matter
if you believe it or not.

427
00:23:47,240 --> 00:23:48,536
Just for fun.

428
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:51,480
Honestly, I don't
really believe it either.

429
00:23:51,480 --> 00:23:54,160
I just want to get some information

430
00:23:54,160 --> 00:23:56,120
to make my comic more fun.

431
00:23:56,120 --> 00:23:57,996
Then go have fun by yourself.

432
00:23:58,640 --> 00:23:59,640
I'm not going.

433
00:24:00,412 --> 00:24:03,152
Come on. I want you to go with me.

434
00:24:03,152 --> 00:24:04,365
No.

435
00:24:04,390 --> 00:24:06,003
- Please?
- No.

436
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:15,960
Hey.

437
00:24:16,835 --> 00:24:20,364
Isn't that the tarot reader
from last time?

438
00:24:20,939 --> 00:24:22,886
He changed his style?

439
00:24:23,286 --> 00:24:24,286
Yeah.

440
00:24:25,176 --> 00:24:29,560
The competition must be fierce.

441
00:24:32,040 --> 00:24:34,200
What god is he channeling?

442
00:24:35,087 --> 00:24:38,840
The God of Epilepsy?

443
00:24:39,105 --> 00:24:40,271
Jee...

444
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:50,760
I am Lord Bao of Kaifeng.

445
00:25:15,886 --> 00:25:18,935
There's no such thing
as God Lord Bao.

446
00:25:18,960 --> 00:25:21,203
There's only God Guan Yu.

447
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:22,760
Why not?

448
00:25:23,280 --> 00:25:26,781
Lord Bao did so many good deeds.

449
00:25:26,781 --> 00:25:30,455
When he died,
he became a god in heaven.

450
00:25:30,480 --> 00:25:32,280
- Really?
- Yeah.

451
00:25:32,777 --> 00:25:37,051
God Guan Yu was
a real historical figure

452
00:25:37,076 --> 00:25:38,756
while Lord Bao

453
00:25:39,513 --> 00:25:40,640
with the black face

454
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:43,695
and the crescent moon
on his forehead

455
00:25:43,720 --> 00:25:46,765
was added later to make
the TV show entertaining.

456
00:25:46,765 --> 00:25:47,898
Let's just watch.

457
00:25:47,898 --> 00:25:49,352
I want to go home.

458
00:25:49,352 --> 00:25:51,000
- Wait.
- It's too weird.

459
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:54,022
Jee, should we just leave?

460
00:25:54,047 --> 00:25:56,836
Let's stay. It's fun.

461
00:25:57,520 --> 00:25:58,520
Jee is staying.

462
00:25:59,320 --> 00:26:00,413
But I'm leaving.

463
00:26:07,558 --> 00:26:15,575
♪ Sacred powers inspire
The vast sky opens ♪

464
00:26:15,600 --> 00:26:19,169
♪ Luck is inevitable ♪

465
00:26:19,194 --> 00:26:24,170
♪ Like unexpected precious gems ♪

466
00:26:24,840 --> 00:26:32,200
♪ As for you, beware of accidents
involving vehicles ♪

467
00:26:33,143 --> 00:26:36,716
♪ Disaster is certain ♪

468
00:26:36,716 --> 00:26:41,689
♪ Your lover will betray you ♪

469
00:26:43,806 --> 00:26:47,871
♪ As for you,
misfortune is upon you ♪

470
00:26:47,896 --> 00:26:52,033
♪ You must perform a ritual
to dispel bad luck ♪

471
00:26:52,058 --> 00:26:55,551
♪ To turn heavy fate into light ♪

472
00:26:55,551 --> 00:27:02,776
♪ Otherwise,
blood will be spilled ♪

473
00:27:04,280 --> 00:27:06,092
Blood will be spilled?

474
00:27:06,117 --> 00:27:08,350
How much for the ritual
to dispel bad luck?

475
00:27:09,599 --> 00:27:11,512
Just 500 baht.

476
00:27:11,512 --> 00:27:12,720
- 5,000 baht.
- What?

477
00:27:13,513 --> 00:27:15,058
5,000 baht?

478
00:27:15,083 --> 00:27:17,200
This is clearly a scam. Let's go.

479
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:18,409
Isn't that too much?

480
00:27:19,600 --> 00:27:21,280
Hey, Jee! No!

481
00:27:21,305 --> 00:27:23,056
5,000 baht. Wait, wait!

482
00:27:23,081 --> 00:27:25,000
Why did you give it to him?

483
00:27:25,025 --> 00:27:27,040
For peace of mind.
But that was so fast.

484
00:27:27,040 --> 00:27:28,920
Whoa, Jee. 5,000 baht.

485
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:31,960
Wait, what about my fortune?

486
00:27:31,985 --> 00:27:34,840
- About your career...
- I haven't even asked yet!

487
00:27:37,180 --> 00:27:38,896
I have the divine eye.

488
00:27:39,293 --> 00:27:41,853
I know what you want to know.

489
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:44,403
Your career...

490
00:27:44,428 --> 00:27:47,293
- Hey.
- Hao la, hao la.

491
00:27:47,293 --> 00:27:50,873
Lord Bao judges
at the Kaifeng Tribunal.

492
00:27:50,898 --> 00:27:53,603
How can he predict the future?
Is he making this up?

493
00:27:54,200 --> 00:27:57,295
You really have
no critical thinking skills.

494
00:27:57,320 --> 00:27:58,910
Do you know critical thinking?

495
00:27:58,935 --> 00:28:02,628
Think about it. Heaven is full of
good people. No bad guys.

496
00:28:02,628 --> 00:28:05,480
Lord Bao has nothing to do.

497
00:28:05,505 --> 00:28:08,024
So he went on
to study fortune telling.

498
00:28:08,024 --> 00:28:10,670
- I see.
- Yeah.

499
00:28:10,670 --> 00:28:12,880
I get it now.

500
00:28:25,907 --> 00:28:28,975
You have outstanding achievements.

501
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:30,810
You are a good person.

502
00:28:30,835 --> 00:28:33,760
Kind, generous,

503
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:35,744
and charitable.

504
00:28:35,769 --> 00:28:38,895
Truly a man of integrity.

505
00:28:38,920 --> 00:28:42,185
You treat your parents well.

506
00:28:42,210 --> 00:28:43,823
Even though...

507
00:28:45,087 --> 00:28:48,787
you can be a bit
arrogant and proud.

508
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:54,553
- Hey.
- I've got goosebumps.

509
00:28:54,553 --> 00:28:56,420
So accurate.

510
00:28:56,420 --> 00:28:59,796
...floating in the middle
of the ocean.

511
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:08,360
Facing storms and waves.
It could sink at any moment.

512
00:29:12,157 --> 00:29:14,560
What should we do, Lord Bao?

513
00:29:14,585 --> 00:29:15,680
Make merit.

514
00:29:17,494 --> 00:29:20,416
- I'm out of cash.
- Make merit, make merit.

515
00:29:21,042 --> 00:29:23,808
- Here, here.
- Oh dear.

516
00:29:25,336 --> 00:29:26,616
Wait, wait.

517
00:29:28,818 --> 00:29:29,905
Hey!

518
00:29:30,821 --> 00:29:33,941
Rest assured.

519
00:29:33,941 --> 00:29:37,481
Once the storm passes...

520
00:29:37,481 --> 00:29:44,559
the little boat will sail
through the obstacles just fine.

521
00:29:44,584 --> 00:29:47,815
And good things will happen.

522
00:29:47,840 --> 00:29:49,520
Trust me.

523
00:29:53,604 --> 00:29:54,604
Hey!

524
00:30:03,323 --> 00:30:04,496
Is he dead?

525
00:30:11,034 --> 00:30:12,421
Chon,

526
00:30:12,421 --> 00:30:14,760
was all that real?

527
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:18,280
What's your critical thinking say?

528
00:30:19,146 --> 00:30:22,386
Based on my critical thinking...

529
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:25,372
I think the fortune teller is...

530
00:30:26,489 --> 00:30:27,971
- totally faking it.
- I knew it.

531
00:30:27,996 --> 00:30:30,410
A total scam. Think about it...

532
00:30:31,066 --> 00:30:33,346
Nidnoi betraying me?

533
00:30:34,480 --> 00:30:36,680
You wouldn't do that, right?

534
00:30:36,680 --> 00:30:39,693
- Exactly. It's nonsense.
- Yeah.

535
00:30:41,935 --> 00:30:43,235
- Come on, Jee.
- Hmm.

536
00:30:51,404 --> 00:30:54,920
♪ Luck is inevitable ♪

537
00:30:55,832 --> 00:30:57,760
- Huh?
- 10 Baht.

538
00:31:00,697 --> 00:31:01,936
10 Baht.

539
00:31:02,650 --> 00:31:03,880
Unexpected luck.

540
00:31:05,120 --> 00:31:07,200
Oh, just 10 Baht?

541
00:31:08,840 --> 00:31:12,040
For someone who
wins the lottery often,

542
00:31:12,040 --> 00:31:16,175
and gets door prizes like you
will never understand.

543
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:20,240
For me,
getting anything is never easy.

544
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:23,680
Every baht, every cent, comes
from my blood, sweat, and tears.

545
00:31:23,680 --> 00:31:26,280
I'm exhausted
working myself to the bone.

546
00:31:26,280 --> 00:31:29,655
But look at this, 10 Baht for free.

547
00:31:29,680 --> 00:31:32,490
- 10 Baht for nothing!
- Darling.

548
00:31:32,515 --> 00:31:36,102
- You are the luckiest person ever.
- Yes.

549
00:31:36,127 --> 00:31:38,480
- Truly.
- So lucky.

550
00:31:39,726 --> 00:31:41,373
- Hey!
- What?

551
00:31:41,373 --> 00:31:43,491
♪ Blood will be spilled ♪
Ohn, wait...

552
00:31:43,516 --> 00:31:45,160
- Hey!
- You're bleeding!

553
00:31:45,185 --> 00:31:48,572
Use your two fingers.
Breathe through your mouth.

554
00:31:48,572 --> 00:31:50,092
Keep pinching it.

555
00:31:50,092 --> 00:31:53,520
Lord Bao predicted
blood would be spilled.

556
00:31:53,520 --> 00:31:56,065
This is just a nosebleed.

557
00:31:56,065 --> 00:31:58,855
Actually, maybe...

558
00:31:58,880 --> 00:32:01,560
you could've been having a stroke!

559
00:32:01,560 --> 00:32:04,619
But you already made merit,
so now it was just a nosebleed.

560
00:32:04,644 --> 00:32:06,800
You make it sound so scary.

561
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:08,750
Well, isn't it true?

562
00:32:09,797 --> 00:32:12,067
- Keep pinching it.
- Still bleeding.

563
00:32:12,092 --> 00:32:14,759
- Let's go eat. I'm hungry.
- Let's go sit down.

564
00:32:16,600 --> 00:32:19,516
Excuse me, can we have menus?

565
00:32:20,379 --> 00:32:21,379
Hey.

566
00:32:22,137 --> 00:32:23,430
I'll just get it myself.

567
00:32:27,760 --> 00:32:29,490
Can I have some menus?

568
00:32:30,546 --> 00:32:33,453
♪ Accident involving vehicles ♪
Ouch! That hurts!

569
00:32:33,453 --> 00:32:35,564
- Sorry.
- This is not a playground.

570
00:32:35,564 --> 00:32:37,765
I really didn't mean to.
I'm really sorry.

571
00:32:37,765 --> 00:32:39,560
Where are your parents?

572
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:41,015
I'm sorry.

573
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:43,455
Accident involving vehicles.

574
00:32:43,480 --> 00:32:46,080
It's okay, dear.
She didn't mean to scold you.

575
00:32:46,105 --> 00:32:48,280
- Be careful next time, okay?
- Yes.

576
00:32:48,280 --> 00:32:52,343
Hey, why are you siding with him?

577
00:32:52,368 --> 00:32:55,235
The injured person is right here.
Shouldn't you be comforting me?

578
00:32:55,235 --> 00:32:57,375
He's just a child.

579
00:32:57,400 --> 00:32:59,464
So what?
That doesn't make him right.

580
00:32:59,489 --> 00:33:03,649
So the adult is
the only one at fault?

581
00:33:03,649 --> 00:33:06,910
Honey, don't be unreasonable.

582
00:33:08,180 --> 00:33:10,260
Betrayed by a life partner.

583
00:33:11,740 --> 00:33:16,520
♪ Your lover will betray you ♪

584
00:33:20,986 --> 00:33:22,360
Hangry again.

585
00:33:24,720 --> 00:33:25,833
- Chon.
- Huh?

586
00:33:25,833 --> 00:33:29,600
I think Lord Bao got you.

587
00:33:33,323 --> 00:33:35,240
- Hey!
- What?

588
00:33:36,511 --> 00:33:38,920
Speak of the devil.

589
00:33:39,680 --> 00:33:41,000
New outfit too.

590
00:33:41,749 --> 00:33:43,160
Full Bohemian style.

591
00:33:44,413 --> 00:33:45,800
Alright, have a seat, Mom.

592
00:33:46,378 --> 00:33:48,378
Menus please.

593
00:33:50,140 --> 00:33:52,000
Why do they get to order before us?

594
00:33:54,040 --> 00:33:55,560
Divine privilege.

595
00:34:00,879 --> 00:34:03,712
- Want this? This looks good.
- What do you want, Jee?

596
00:34:04,549 --> 00:34:06,543
- One grilled chicken, please.
- Hmm.

597
00:34:06,567 --> 00:34:08,955
- Must be hungry.
- And winged bean salad.

598
00:34:08,955 --> 00:34:10,642
Very hungry

599
00:34:14,495 --> 00:34:16,000
I'm going to the restroom.

600
00:34:17,377 --> 00:34:19,360
- What will you have, Jee?
- Hmm...

601
00:34:19,385 --> 00:34:21,290
- Anything else?
- This looks good too.

602
00:34:22,008 --> 00:34:23,280
I'm going to the restroom.

603
00:34:26,886 --> 00:34:30,200
Stir-fried kale with salted fish.

604
00:34:35,400 --> 00:34:36,687
- Oh!
- Oops!

605
00:34:36,687 --> 00:34:37,947
We meet again.

606
00:34:37,947 --> 00:34:39,773
Who are you?

607
00:34:39,773 --> 00:34:41,960
You've just read my fortune.

608
00:34:43,019 --> 00:34:45,185
Don't recognize you at all.

609
00:34:45,210 --> 00:34:47,680
Once the spirit leaves,
I forget everything.

610
00:34:47,680 --> 00:34:49,317
I can't remember a thing.

611
00:34:49,317 --> 00:34:50,644
- Excuse me.
- Hold on.

612
00:34:50,644 --> 00:34:53,516
You predicted my girlfriend
would have good luck.

613
00:34:54,240 --> 00:34:56,653
Wait a minute.

614
00:34:56,653 --> 00:34:59,365
Was she your girlfriend?

615
00:34:59,365 --> 00:35:01,765
Oh no! I thought
it was the other one.

616
00:35:01,765 --> 00:35:03,760
My gaydar is so broken.

617
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:07,020
Busted! You said
you couldn't remember.

618
00:35:07,020 --> 00:35:08,065
Oops!

619
00:35:10,833 --> 00:35:12,223
There's no spirit, right?

620
00:35:12,248 --> 00:35:14,240
You're a scammer, aren't you?

621
00:35:14,840 --> 00:35:19,600
Why do you have to exploit beliefs

622
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:21,819
and other people's misfortune?

623
00:35:21,844 --> 00:35:23,387
Have you no shame?

624
00:35:23,387 --> 00:35:28,073
Fine! Okay, I admit it.
I don't have a spirit.

625
00:35:28,098 --> 00:35:31,301
But who would listen to
a kathoey fortune teller like me?

626
00:35:31,326 --> 00:35:34,840
We have to create a story.
Make it sound mystical.

627
00:35:34,840 --> 00:35:37,387
Once I say I'm possessed,

628
00:35:37,387 --> 00:35:38,893
people listen.

629
00:35:38,893 --> 00:35:39,901
See?

630
00:35:40,360 --> 00:35:43,410
But I really am a fortune teller.

631
00:35:43,410 --> 00:35:45,770
Earlier this year,
I was in a car accident.

632
00:35:45,770 --> 00:35:47,583
And when I woke up

633
00:35:47,583 --> 00:35:49,320
I had the divine eye!

634
00:35:49,320 --> 00:35:50,516
Still making excuses!

635
00:35:52,529 --> 00:35:53,960
Sir.

636
00:35:54,660 --> 00:35:56,960
- Do you want me to tell the truth?
- Hmm.

637
00:35:56,960 --> 00:36:00,320
Your fortune is terrible.
So bad I don't even want to say it.

638
00:36:00,320 --> 00:36:02,727
It would just destroy your morale.

639
00:36:02,727 --> 00:36:08,320
I'm telling you, there is no
temple or chant that can help you.

640
00:36:08,320 --> 00:36:10,273
You can find a new job right now.

641
00:36:10,273 --> 00:36:12,880
But I asked you for money

642
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:15,830
is because I've got
my family to feed.

643
00:36:15,855 --> 00:36:19,424
I'm really sorry.
But here I have this for you.

644
00:36:19,465 --> 00:36:24,335
This right here.
The Sacred Beckoning Cat Talisman.

645
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:29,320
Fully consecrated by my temple.

646
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:33,480
Keep it to for luck, fortune,
happiness, and prosperity.

647
00:36:33,480 --> 00:36:38,040
Once the rainstorm passes
may only good things come to you.

648
00:36:38,040 --> 00:36:40,167
No, I don't want it. It's fine.

649
00:36:40,167 --> 00:36:43,533
Trying to scam me again?
I don't want them.

650
00:36:43,533 --> 00:36:45,173
Sir, just take it.

651
00:36:45,173 --> 00:36:47,760
Think of it as a souvenir
from one team-carrier to another.

652
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:49,520
Just by looking at you...

653
00:36:49,520 --> 00:36:52,891
From the look in your eyes
and the weight you're carrying,

654
00:36:52,916 --> 00:36:54,947
I know that you are
the one carrying all the load.

655
00:36:54,947 --> 00:36:58,810
Only fellow team-carrier like us
can recognize each other.

656
00:37:02,040 --> 00:37:04,743
The weight you're carrying

657
00:37:04,768 --> 00:37:08,055
part of it comes
from your own pressure.

658
00:37:08,080 --> 00:37:09,535
Why is that?

659
00:37:09,560 --> 00:37:12,055
Oh, I see.

660
00:37:12,080 --> 00:37:14,167
You're the eldest son
of a Chinese family.

661
00:37:14,167 --> 00:37:16,147
But you can't give
your parents grandchildren.

662
00:37:16,147 --> 00:37:18,803
So you carry everything
on your own shoulders.

663
00:37:20,546 --> 00:37:22,046
Hang in there.

664
00:37:23,560 --> 00:37:25,723
Scammer gangs like you

665
00:37:26,311 --> 00:37:27,584
I don't believe you.

666
00:37:27,584 --> 00:37:29,960
If you don't believe, then don't.

667
00:37:31,081 --> 00:37:32,680
Is there a problem, Sis?

668
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:36,560
No.

669
00:37:39,920 --> 00:37:41,141
- Sis.
- Hmm?

670
00:37:41,571 --> 00:37:43,103
Is this guy bothering you?

671
00:37:43,493 --> 00:37:44,880
No problems at all.

672
00:37:46,880 --> 00:37:48,760
Then let's go eat.
The food is here.

673
00:37:49,240 --> 00:37:50,973
Let's go.

674
00:37:51,803 --> 00:37:53,096
I'm hungry.

675
00:38:08,400 --> 00:38:09,400
Hello, Gift.

676
00:38:10,680 --> 00:38:11,680
Jee.

677
00:38:12,793 --> 00:38:13,806
Hmm?

678
00:38:14,817 --> 00:38:16,520
I'm really sorry.

679
00:38:32,918 --> 00:38:34,783
- Hey.
- Jee, come on.

680
00:38:34,808 --> 00:38:37,207
- You took so long.
- Hey, this is delicious.

681
00:38:37,862 --> 00:38:40,442
- I saved you this.
- Where's the serving spoon?

682
00:38:40,442 --> 00:38:43,081
Use it for the eggs.

683
00:38:46,489 --> 00:38:49,400
These two will eat it all up.

684
00:38:54,491 --> 00:38:55,491
Jee...

685
00:38:56,397 --> 00:38:58,030
What's wrong?
Why aren't you eating?

686
00:39:02,965 --> 00:39:03,965
What?

687
00:39:03,990 --> 00:39:06,560
- Why are you crying?
- What's wrong?

688
00:39:07,520 --> 00:39:09,640
- What happened?
- Jee...

689
00:39:09,640 --> 00:39:11,023
Whatever it is, tell me.

690
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:17,440
Jee, what's wrong?

691
00:39:17,440 --> 00:39:18,936
Tell me, what is it?

692
00:39:21,869 --> 00:39:23,015
Why are you crying?

693
00:39:28,558 --> 00:39:31,560
Oh dear. Don't cry.

694
00:39:31,585 --> 00:39:34,520
Don't cry, Jee.

695
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:40,493
What did you say to him
to make him cry like that?

696
00:39:40,493 --> 00:39:44,280
I just told him he'd lose his job.
But he didn't believe me.

697
00:39:44,695 --> 00:39:46,199
Crying like that...

698
00:39:46,795 --> 00:39:48,552
He must really lose his job.

699
00:39:49,121 --> 00:39:52,840
Our Jakkrit was chosen
by the god himself.

700
00:39:53,336 --> 00:39:54,656
How could he not be accurate?

701
00:39:55,280 --> 00:39:57,640
Who dares to disrespect Jakkrit?

702
00:39:58,227 --> 00:40:01,717
Dad, can you please call me
by the name I want to be called?

703
00:40:01,742 --> 00:40:04,788
- Janjao, Janjao, Janjao.
- Okay.

704
00:40:04,813 --> 00:40:07,560
Janjao, let's eat, dear.

705
00:40:07,560 --> 00:40:10,006
This is delicious.
Let me get you some.

706
00:40:10,031 --> 00:40:12,816
Be more like Mom. Call me Janjao.

707
00:40:13,252 --> 00:40:15,063
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

708
00:40:15,088 --> 00:40:17,055
- Love you the most, Mom.
- Yes, dear.

709
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:18,720
Hey, Sis.

710
00:40:19,440 --> 00:40:21,920
When will the spirit give us
winning lottery numbers?

711
00:40:22,680 --> 00:40:26,440
Yeah. Just one big prize is enough.

712
00:40:27,311 --> 00:40:30,123
Dad, using powers for
personal gain like this...

713
00:40:30,714 --> 00:40:32,950
the god will be furious.

714
00:40:32,975 --> 00:40:38,495
Yes, with great power
comes great responsibility.

715
00:40:38,520 --> 00:40:40,120
That's right, Mom.

716
00:40:44,756 --> 00:40:45,920
Don't cry, Jee.

717
00:41:06,637 --> 00:41:07,637
Jee.

718
00:41:10,224 --> 00:41:11,409
Mom?

719
00:41:11,434 --> 00:41:12,457
- Oh!
- Hello, Mom.

720
00:41:12,457 --> 00:41:13,474
Hello.

721
00:41:14,510 --> 00:41:16,535
Why didn't you
tell us you were coming?

722
00:41:16,560 --> 00:41:18,480
I was just about to call.

723
00:41:18,480 --> 00:41:21,387
I was in the neighborhood,
so I bought some durian for you.

724
00:41:21,387 --> 00:41:24,535
I don't eat durian.

725
00:41:24,560 --> 00:41:28,320
I know, but Ohn does.
You like it, right dear?

726
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:30,723
Yes, Mom.

727
00:41:32,720 --> 00:41:36,415
Can we take it up the elevator?

728
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:39,720
It's wrapped in
so many layers. It's fine.

729
00:41:41,756 --> 00:41:44,962
I'll carry it up the stairs myself.

730
00:41:44,987 --> 00:41:47,560
- Thank you. Thank you.
- Sure.

731
00:41:53,880 --> 00:41:54,880
Let's go.

732
00:41:56,571 --> 00:41:57,720
Let's go up.

733
00:42:01,216 --> 00:42:02,920
- Come on.
- Hmm.

734
00:42:04,840 --> 00:42:07,740
Hurry up. I've been
waiting so long. My legs are tired.

735
00:42:18,223 --> 00:42:20,080
Please come in, Mom.

736
00:42:47,624 --> 00:42:50,376
Clean and tidy as always.

737
00:42:52,941 --> 00:42:56,815
Are you inspecting, Mom?

738
00:42:56,840 --> 00:42:58,360
Not at all.

739
00:42:59,500 --> 00:43:02,495
What would you like to drink, Mom?

740
00:43:02,520 --> 00:43:04,130
Tea, coffee, or something else?

741
00:43:04,493 --> 00:43:05,720
- Uh...
- No need, Ohn.

742
00:43:06,658 --> 00:43:09,503
I'll take care of her.
You go take a shower.

743
00:43:10,586 --> 00:43:12,919
- You sure?
- Yes. You go ahead.

744
00:43:48,256 --> 00:43:49,440
- Mom.
- Hmm?

745
00:43:50,560 --> 00:43:53,200
- I lost my job.
- How come?

746
00:43:54,040 --> 00:43:57,200
The company is losing money.

747
00:43:58,160 --> 00:43:59,823
So they have to downsize.

748
00:44:00,304 --> 00:44:05,200
It's not right now, though.
They'd give me a month's notice.

749
00:44:06,078 --> 00:44:07,360
Are you okay?

750
00:44:07,880 --> 00:44:08,880
I'm fine.

751
00:44:09,482 --> 00:44:14,480
But I probably can't help much
with the house renovation anymore.

752
00:44:15,320 --> 00:44:17,440
I don't know
when I'll get a new job.

753
00:44:18,392 --> 00:44:22,432
And the money I send
you and Dad every month...

754
00:44:23,160 --> 00:44:25,160
from now on, I might...

755
00:44:25,160 --> 00:44:27,210
It's okay.

756
00:44:27,760 --> 00:44:31,680
You don't have to
give us money anymore.

757
00:44:31,705 --> 00:44:35,945
No, I might just
send less in the future.

758
00:44:36,592 --> 00:44:39,420
And about the house renovation,

759
00:44:39,445 --> 00:44:41,287
Dad and I can fix it ourselves.

760
00:44:41,312 --> 00:44:44,143
We still have plenty
of the money you gave us.

761
00:44:44,709 --> 00:44:46,719
That was for personal use.

762
00:44:46,744 --> 00:44:49,101
Isn't fixing the house
a personal matter?

763
00:44:49,101 --> 00:44:50,121
Hmm.

764
00:44:50,121 --> 00:44:53,967
Do you know that Dad never
spends the money you give him?

765
00:44:53,967 --> 00:44:56,081
He saves every single baht.

766
00:44:56,081 --> 00:45:00,200
He said when you're in trouble
he'll give this money back to you.

767
00:45:02,765 --> 00:45:07,430
Don't worry about it.
Same goes for our health.

768
00:45:08,040 --> 00:45:11,240
The insurance you got
for us covers everything.

769
00:45:15,920 --> 00:45:17,040
But what if...

770
00:45:18,320 --> 00:45:19,320
if I...

771
00:45:21,232 --> 00:45:23,832
can't pay the premium this year?

772
00:45:26,080 --> 00:45:28,560
You're not my only child, you know.

773
00:45:30,320 --> 00:45:32,760
Why do you have to
carry everything alone?

774
00:45:34,419 --> 00:45:36,400
Come on.

775
00:45:37,221 --> 00:45:38,393
Jiroj...

776
00:45:39,310 --> 00:45:40,560
despite how he seems...

777
00:45:41,654 --> 00:45:45,875
he's more reliable than you think.

778
00:45:45,900 --> 00:45:48,335
You don't have to
carry it all alone.

779
00:45:56,811 --> 00:45:58,200
And if...

780
00:46:00,440 --> 00:46:04,830
things get really bad,
just rent out this condo,

781
00:46:05,440 --> 00:46:06,960
and move back home.

782
00:46:15,104 --> 00:46:16,660
Can Ohn come too?

783
00:46:20,512 --> 00:46:23,378
Of course, son. Ohn too.

784
00:46:23,403 --> 00:46:25,064
It'll be warm and lively.

785
00:46:27,111 --> 00:46:28,575
Are you sure?

786
00:46:28,600 --> 00:46:30,240
Absolutely!

787
00:46:52,773 --> 00:46:54,213
I feel bad for Jee.

788
00:46:54,770 --> 00:46:56,560
Look on the bright side...

789
00:46:57,333 --> 00:46:59,880
At least now he knows
how to move forward with his life.

790
00:47:00,520 --> 00:47:03,080
Being stuck in limbo

791
00:47:03,080 --> 00:47:04,440
is the most torturous thing.

792
00:47:05,103 --> 00:47:07,080
That's true.

793
00:47:08,280 --> 00:47:10,520
Reminds me of us during COVID.

794
00:47:11,720 --> 00:47:15,120
That time was the worst.

795
00:47:15,973 --> 00:47:18,130
My tattoo shop had zero customers.

796
00:47:19,400 --> 00:47:22,520
But your work
at the hospital was crazy.

797
00:47:22,520 --> 00:47:26,695
It was killing me back then.
Thought we wouldn't make it.

798
00:47:26,720 --> 00:47:30,296
And patients were fighting
for beds like musical chairs.

799
00:47:31,288 --> 00:47:34,313
That time was absolutely terrible.

800
00:47:35,159 --> 00:47:36,710
We had no money.

801
00:47:37,200 --> 00:47:40,623
We couldn't see
or even talk to each other.

802
00:47:41,437 --> 00:47:42,563
Come on.

803
00:47:44,546 --> 00:47:46,416
We got through it, didn't we?

804
00:47:49,240 --> 00:47:52,316
That's because you
stayed with me and didn't leave.

805
00:47:52,933 --> 00:47:54,040
Hmm...

806
00:47:55,082 --> 00:47:57,760
And because I have you too.

807
00:48:01,720 --> 00:48:04,440
- Thank you.
- Thank you too.

808
00:48:04,798 --> 00:48:05,798
Yeah.

809
00:48:09,480 --> 00:48:10,480
Let's go.

810
00:48:13,240 --> 00:48:15,326
- Hey, wait.
- Yeah?

811
00:48:16,200 --> 00:48:20,848
Come to think of it, during COVID,
you're really into fortune tellers.

812
00:48:20,873 --> 00:48:21,993
Really?

813
00:48:22,555 --> 00:48:27,242
Historically, they say
whenever the world is in chaos

814
00:48:27,242 --> 00:48:31,230
economic depression,
wars, things like that

815
00:48:31,255 --> 00:48:34,120
people turn to fortune telling.

816
00:48:34,120 --> 00:48:35,740
Looking for spiritual guidance.

817
00:48:35,740 --> 00:48:39,109
Well, it helps. It's comforting.

818
00:48:39,134 --> 00:48:40,986
They usually only say good things.

819
00:48:40,986 --> 00:48:42,280
Things that are...

820
00:48:43,095 --> 00:48:46,762
hopeful that it will pass.
And we'll get something good.

821
00:48:46,762 --> 00:48:49,527
- Hmm, really?
- Hmm.

822
00:48:49,552 --> 00:48:52,707
But about the accuracy...

823
00:48:52,732 --> 00:48:55,856
Actually, they speak broadly.

824
00:48:56,350 --> 00:48:58,415
They cast a wide net.

825
00:48:58,440 --> 00:49:02,680
We are the ones
who interpret it to fit ourselves.

826
00:49:02,705 --> 00:49:06,810
And think they are talking
specifically about us.

827
00:49:07,206 --> 00:49:09,251
There's a term for this.

828
00:49:09,276 --> 00:49:14,110
It's called the Barnum Effect.

829
00:49:14,775 --> 00:49:17,975
When the fortune teller told me

830
00:49:18,000 --> 00:49:20,435
I would get
unexpected luck. Remember?

831
00:49:20,460 --> 00:49:21,460
I did get it, though.

832
00:49:22,160 --> 00:49:24,307
But it's just speaking broadly.

833
00:49:24,332 --> 00:49:28,455
Think about it. They didn't
specify a time or place at all.

834
00:49:28,480 --> 00:49:30,486
They didn't even say
what I would get.

835
00:49:31,000 --> 00:49:33,959
But for us, the moment
we saw the 10-baht coin,

836
00:49:33,984 --> 00:49:37,147
we interpreted it
as accurate ourselves.

837
00:49:37,172 --> 00:49:40,713
Get it?
Or when a fortune teller tells us

838
00:49:40,738 --> 00:49:44,580
You are a very kind person.

839
00:49:44,605 --> 00:49:47,492
But if you get betrayed,

840
00:49:47,517 --> 00:49:50,070
you'll get angry
and hold a deep grudge.

841
00:49:50,095 --> 00:49:51,359
Honestly,

842
00:49:51,359 --> 00:49:53,488
isn't that how people are?

843
00:49:53,488 --> 00:49:56,120
Hmm, that's true.

844
00:49:57,320 --> 00:49:59,880
You really live up
to your science background.

845
00:50:02,066 --> 00:50:03,407
Do you know...

846
00:50:03,432 --> 00:50:07,255
which type of prophecy
I like the most?

847
00:50:07,280 --> 00:50:10,648
- Ooh, I don't want to guess.
- Seriously.

848
00:50:10,648 --> 00:50:12,503
Just tell me.

849
00:50:13,207 --> 00:50:14,647
- Which one?
- Okay.

850
00:50:15,060 --> 00:50:19,596
I like predicting the future
based on the orbits of the stars.

851
00:50:20,997 --> 00:50:22,676
- Stars?
- Hmm.

852
00:50:22,700 --> 00:50:25,375
What do stars
have to do with our lives?

853
00:50:25,400 --> 00:50:26,920
That's not scientific at all.

854
00:50:29,244 --> 00:50:32,080
It is. It helps comfort us.

855
00:50:34,461 --> 00:50:35,521
Like how...

856
00:50:36,201 --> 00:50:38,427
Damn you, Mercury!
Something like that?

857
00:50:38,427 --> 00:50:39,693
No.

858
00:50:40,358 --> 00:50:43,360
It tells us that
endure a bit longer,

859
00:50:44,077 --> 00:50:45,372
soon the stars

860
00:50:45,950 --> 00:50:49,130
will move to a new position.

861
00:50:50,621 --> 00:50:51,760
Okay.

862
00:50:52,980 --> 00:50:56,323
Hang in there.
The stars will move soon.

863
00:51:19,680 --> 00:51:20,680
What are you looking at?

864
00:51:23,138 --> 00:51:26,920
I already brushed my teeth.

865
00:51:26,944 --> 00:51:28,944
Oh boy...

866
00:51:28,952 --> 00:51:31,490
But the durian smell
is still on the breath.

867
00:51:36,732 --> 00:51:38,038
- Jee...
- Mmm.

868
00:51:38,782 --> 00:51:40,440
If finding a job is too hard...

869
00:51:41,797 --> 00:51:43,803
have you considered
starting your own business?

870
00:51:44,440 --> 00:51:45,440
Oh boy.

871
00:51:46,455 --> 00:51:49,703
Investing right now isn't easy.

872
00:51:51,044 --> 00:51:52,920
Hmm, true.

873
00:51:54,120 --> 00:51:56,233
But no matter what you do next...

874
00:51:57,420 --> 00:51:59,335
you have me by your side.

875
00:51:59,360 --> 00:52:02,006
- You know that, right?
- I know. But right now...

876
00:52:03,131 --> 00:52:06,345
- Keep your distance.
- I was just getting sentimental.

877
00:52:07,671 --> 00:52:10,023
I can't think right now.

878
00:52:10,600 --> 00:52:12,656
I've been a company
worker for so long.

879
00:52:13,523 --> 00:52:15,080
I don't know
how to do anything else.

880
00:52:16,310 --> 00:52:19,335
Well, you get to try new things.

881
00:52:19,360 --> 00:52:22,006
- Open up to new experiences.
- At 50 years old?

882
00:52:23,907 --> 00:52:27,076
Consider this your break.

883
00:52:27,101 --> 00:52:29,175
Relax for a bit.

884
00:52:29,200 --> 00:52:31,336
You've worked hard for so long.

885
00:52:31,840 --> 00:52:33,573
Okay? Rest a bit.

886
00:52:33,573 --> 00:52:36,910
No need to rush into any decisions.

887
00:52:40,001 --> 00:52:41,001
Rest.

888
00:52:43,040 --> 00:52:44,800
What is that?

889
00:52:45,615 --> 00:52:46,615
- This?
- Hmm.

890
00:52:46,640 --> 00:52:47,640
Oh.

891
00:52:48,248 --> 00:52:50,040
It's a cat talisman.

892
00:52:51,353 --> 00:52:53,090
The medium gave it to me.

893
00:52:55,230 --> 00:52:56,283
What kind of cat is this?

894
00:52:57,120 --> 00:52:58,960
It couldn't be uglier.

895
00:52:59,948 --> 00:53:01,640
Hey, Jee.

896
00:53:04,320 --> 00:53:06,015
While I was showering,

897
00:53:06,040 --> 00:53:08,200
I came up with
a plot for a new comic.

898
00:53:09,080 --> 00:53:12,935
I'm thinking of a detective comic,

899
00:53:12,960 --> 00:53:15,320
with a cat as the protagonist.

900
00:53:16,900 --> 00:53:18,934
Sherlock Holmes cat.

901
00:53:18,959 --> 00:53:20,360
Lord Bao cat.

902
00:53:20,360 --> 00:53:22,870
Then the cat has to be black.

903
00:53:22,895 --> 00:53:26,015
And there must be Zhan Zhao cat,

904
00:53:26,040 --> 00:53:28,603
Wang Chao, Ma Han,
Zhang Long, and Zhao Hu cats.

905
00:53:29,520 --> 00:53:30,520
Where...

906
00:53:31,105 --> 00:53:33,072
dogs are the villains.

907
00:53:33,072 --> 00:53:35,298
- Is that good?
- Hmm.

908
00:53:35,298 --> 00:53:38,311
Bring out the Dog Head Guillotine!

909
00:53:41,655 --> 00:53:45,332
I guarantee it. Dog slaves,
cat slaves will go crazy for it.

910
00:53:45,357 --> 00:53:47,279
It'll definitely sell well.

911
00:53:49,104 --> 00:53:50,577
- Umm...
- Hmm?

912
00:53:51,087 --> 00:53:53,274
Babe, don't you worry.

913
00:53:53,274 --> 00:53:56,095
Daddy Ohn will take care of you.

914
00:53:56,120 --> 00:53:58,880
Daddy will spoil you
to your heart's content.

915
00:54:00,125 --> 00:54:01,498
You're getting carried away.

916
00:54:01,920 --> 00:54:04,200
But right now,
I'm moving in with my mom.

917
00:54:04,654 --> 00:54:07,727
Hey, Jee, don't go!

918
00:54:07,727 --> 00:54:10,720
Come back and let me repay you

919
00:54:10,720 --> 00:54:13,273
for setting up the page
so people follow my comics.

920
00:54:13,298 --> 00:54:15,958
Come back and let me
repay you with my love.

921
00:54:15,958 --> 00:54:18,280
If you wanted to repay me,
you shouldn't have eated durian.

922
00:54:18,280 --> 00:54:19,960
Gosh, you're obsessed with it.

923
00:54:19,960 --> 00:54:23,000
Farewell. Bye-bye.

924
00:54:23,025 --> 00:54:25,240
No, Jee! No...

925
00:54:25,264 --> 00:54:28,040
Jee, come back!

926
00:54:30,861 --> 00:54:33,000
I love my boyfriend.

927
00:54:34,440 --> 00:54:36,160
But I love durian too.

928
00:55:32,640 --> 00:55:33,720
I just...

929
00:55:34,517 --> 00:55:35,920
don't want to go to Nakhon Nayok.

930
00:55:37,400 --> 00:55:38,760
Grandma's house...

931
00:55:40,227 --> 00:55:41,560
Dong Lakhon.

932
00:55:42,680 --> 00:55:43,680
Dad.

933
00:55:45,680 --> 00:55:46,680
Whose dad?

934
00:55:48,103 --> 00:55:50,180
Come out to Grandma.

935
00:55:50,205 --> 00:55:52,200
Ohn, can you hear me, son?

936
00:55:52,225 --> 00:55:53,225
Ohn.

937
00:55:54,480 --> 00:55:56,240
Ohn, Dad's here. Can you hear me?

938
00:55:57,069 --> 00:55:58,280
We're right here with you.

939
00:56:03,000 --> 00:56:08,080
♪ Can you feel
that love still remains? ♪

940
00:56:08,080 --> 00:56:14,400
♪ Can you feel
the stories we made? ♪

941
00:56:14,400 --> 00:56:19,591
♪ No matter what stood in our way ♪

942
00:56:19,615 --> 00:56:23,127
♪ Come rain or shine ♪

943
00:56:23,152 --> 00:56:28,360
♪ Can you feel
the love from the start? ♪

944
00:56:28,360 --> 00:56:34,680
♪ Can you feel
the beat of my heart? ♪

945
00:56:34,680 --> 00:56:40,160
♪ Calling out so we never part ♪

946
00:56:40,160 --> 00:56:44,760
♪ Every day together
just you and I ♪

947
00:56:44,760 --> 00:56:49,760
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

948
00:56:49,760 --> 00:56:52,372
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

949
00:56:52,396 --> 00:56:54,396
Subtitle by Trirat Trakulphat
